obo:ECO_0006054  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2146  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Neto1 is an integral membrane protein which localizes to the postsynaptic density membrane in hippocampal neurons.\n\nFig.2: \"Neto1 is a PSD Protein Localized to Dendritic Spines and Interacts with PSD-95 through a C-Terminal PDZ Tripeptide\"\n- Fig.2A: \"Neto1 was prominently expressed in the crude synaptosomal (Figure 2A, lane S2) and PSD fractions, but was absent from the synaptic vesicle fraction (Figure 2A, lane LP2).\"\n- Fig.2B/C/D: \"We found that Neto1 immunostaining decorated MAP2 positive dendritic arbors and co-localized with that of PSD-95 (Figure 2B) and NR1 (Figure 2C). We also found that Neto1 co-localized with actin (Figure 2D), which is highly enriched in dendritic spines in the hippocampus [20].\"\n- Fig.2E/F: \"Altogether, these findings indicate that Neto1 associates with PSD-95 in brain synapses through the binding of its C-terminal tripeptide with the PDZ domains of PSD-95\"\nConclusion: \"Together, these findings demonstrate that Neto1 is a component of the PSD of excitatory synapses.\"\n\n12/12/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - Over-expressed Neto1 is of mouse species: \"Full-length mouse Neto1 cDNAs were obtained by reverse transcription\"\n- Fractionation is performed on mouse species: \"Subcellular fractionation of mouse brains was performed as described \"\n- Dissociated cultures were of mouse species: \"Acutely dissociated hippocampal CA1 neurons were obtained from Neto1 +/+ and Neto1 tlz/tlz mice....\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9783-5183" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5676-366X" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2146" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

